node.text:
Tucked behind the colonial doors of a boutique hotel in New Orleans sits a bar whose enchanting quarters are as tempting as its innovative cocktails and spirits. At the candle-lit haven of Loa — a bar whose name was inspired by the Voodoo word for benevolent deities or holy spirits — the mix of the alluring atmosphere and bartenders’ focus on the heightened qualities of craftsmanship and ritual have been attracting a regular following of the city's creatives, entrepreneurs, and visitors for years. 
@loaneworleans’s bartender Alan Walter is a driving force behind the menu’s creative innovation. As an urban forager, it’s important to him to use local ingredients and be guided by the new flavors he discovers during different seasons. The cocktail menu is curated based on his latest inventions, so stop by the bar — he’s always up for a conversation and sharing the story behind one of his concoctions.

The Beautiful Destinations Team 
Logan Armstrong @loganstrongarms
Chris Shepherd @cshep25
Dzana Ashworth @ladzana

node.text:
Thank you @mellyeatsworld for giving us these cuddly pineapple cakes that just look too good to eat! ❤ Sloths are now being recognized and appreciated just recently, but did you know they played a huge part in the spread of avocado trees in the Americas? 🤔

💡 BC Trivia: The giant ground sloth (the ancestor of the modern sloth) lived during the Cenozoic area. They were one of the herbivores large enough that can swallow avocados whole and excrete its seeds intact! 🤯 As they wandered the Cenozoic era "blessing" the world with avocado seeds, the avocado trees grew in abundance in North and South America and eventually, other parts of the world! If you'll be eating avocados, remember it's because of these easygoing mammals! 🥑

Is the sloth an animal that interests you? Have you seen a sloth up close? 🦥

📸 @mellyeatsworld

Yes, we know you're hungry right now. 🦞 It's okay to admit you watched this reel by @the_crab_shack on repeat because we did too. Picture yourself savoring meaty lobster tails, snow crab legs, juicy shrimp, crawfish, and more!

Have you been to The Crab Shack? Is this something you'd like to try when in California? 🦀

📍 @the_crab_shack, California, USA

node.text:
If you've never tried Japanese soufflé pancakes, let @fufupancakecafe introduce their creative and delicious works of art! 🥞 Their pancakes are not only colorful and visually appealing, but the many flavors they have will surely make you want to come back to try them all. You'll never eat pancakes the same way again! 😋

💡 BC Tip: Try their Japanese fruits sandos, kakigoris, and their lineup of milkteas and uber aesthetic beverages!

Which among the ten are you looking forward to trying? Are you a fan of Japanese sweet treats? 🍽️ 

📸 Fufu Cafe @fufupancakecafe

You won't be able to resist these cruffins from @supermoonbakehouse! ❤️ "What's a cruffin?", you ask? A cruffin is a hybrid of a croissant and a muffin then filled with basically all the good, sweet stuff. 😋

Swipe to see some of the different flavors of Supermoon Bakehouse's cruffins:

1. Ferrero Rocher
2. Key Lime Pie
3. Strawberry-Lychee-Rose
4. Blackberry Mint Jam and Vanilla

Which of these cruffins would you like to try first? Have you tried a cruffin before? ❤️

📸 @supermoonbakehouse

node.text:
This baked feta salmon recipe from @feelgoodfoodie is quick, delicious, and definitely a memorable dish to serve family and friends! 😍 If you're looking for something healthy but packed full of flavor, this recipe is worth keeping in your kitchen arsenal!

𝗜𝗻𝗴𝗿𝗲𝗱𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀:
- salmon
- 1 cup cherry tomatoes, quartered
- 1/4 cup chopped green pepper
- 1/4 cup chopped red onion
- 1 garlic clove, pressed
- 2 tbsp pitted kalamata olives
- 2 cups crumbled feta cheese
- 1/4 tsp salt
- 1/4 ground pepper
- 1/4 tsp oregano (divided) 
- 1/4 tsp red chili flakes
- 1 tbsp extra virgin olive oil
- chopped fresh basil for garnish

𝗜𝗻𝘀𝘁𝗿𝘂𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻𝘀:
- Preheat oven to 400°F. Pat the salmon dry.
- In an oven-safe dish, place the cherry tomatoes, green peppers, red onions, feta cheese, kalamata olives, garlic, half the salt, and half the oregano. Pour the olive oil on top, and toss until well combined.
- Place the salmon in the middle of the baking dish surrounded by all the vegetables. Add the remaining oregano and crushed red pepper on top of the salmon. Drizzle more olive oil if desired.
- Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes, until the tomatoes soften and the salmon is cooked through.
- Add fresh basil leaves and serve with a side of your choice, if desired.

We're looking forward to seeing your takes on this recipe! Would you try this? 😋

📽️ @feelgoodfoodie
